                <head>No. 1189<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Representatives of the United States and Egyptian Governments signed and thereby
                    brought into force two Technical Cooperation Agreements on June 18, 1953. One of
                    them was designed to create an education program and the other was to establish
                    a public health program. For the texts, see TIAS No. 2841, printed in 4 <gloss
                        target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> (pt. 2) 1733 and TIAS No. 2852, printed in 4
                        <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> (pt. 2) 1928.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
